Please compile LLVM static-linked libraries on your machine.

Brief Steps:

1. Download LLVM 2.9( or newer )
	
2. Use CMake to configure projects.

3. Build generated LLVM solution. 
	##### NOTE THAT #####
	## If msvc 8/9/10 was used, please use the same _SCL_SECURE macro definition on your project and llvm.
	
4. Copy toolkit executables from {llvm_build_root}/bin directory to 3rd_party/llvm/toolchains/{platform}
		( platform is win32/x64/linux64 etc. )
		
5. Copy lib files from {llvm_build_root}/lib/{configuration} to 3rd_party/llvm/lib/{environment}
		(
		configuration may be one item of debug/release etc;
		environment is composited by {platform}_{compiler}_{config}, e.g. win32_msvc10_debug 
		)
		
6. Copy folder {llvm_build_root}/include/llvm to 3rd_party/llvm/lib/{env_without_config}/
		(
		env_without_config is composited by {platform}_{compiler}, e.g. win32_msvc10
		)
		
7. Copy folder {llvm_source_root}/include to 3rd_party/llvm

8 .Compile sasl & enjoy it!